に基づいて#にもとづいて#Empt./名＋に基づく、に基づいた＋名、名/Empt./Empt.#Xに基づいてY, using X as an informational basis or reference,(on the basis of X) do Y/X should be something that can act as a reference or basis (the law, data, a plan, a policy, the results of a study etc.)#実際の経験に基づくいい話を聞くことができた。
に沿って#にそって#Empt./名＋に沿う、に沿った＋名、名/Empt./Empt.#Xに沿ってY, to do something Y in line with X, according to X, such that is fits with X, such that it doesn't deviate from X/X should be something that can act as a reference or basis (the law, data, a plan, a policy, the results of a study etc.)/Y describes something done according to X#今、政府の基本方針に沿って今年度の予算案を作っている。/与えられたテーマに沿ってレポートを書き進めてください。
のもとで#Empt.#Empt./名/Empt./Empt.#XのもとでY, taking on the effect X or in the state X, one does something Y/のもとで specifically is used more with people and their effect/Y expresses some action, i.e. the subject does something i.e. NOT something like あの音楽家のもとでピアノが好きになった<-subject is ピアノ-> not correct usage of もとで#チームは今、新しい監督のもとで練習に励んでいる。
のもとに#Empt.#Empt./名/Empt./Empt.#XのもとでY, taking on the effect X or in the state X, one does something Y/のもとに specifically is used more with nouns that express circumstances, conditions or consent/Y expresses some action or state (続いている、平等、など)#校庭のキャンプファイヤーは夏の最大のイベントで、周辺住民の了解のもとに十年も続いている。/開発という名のもとに自然が失われていくのは残念だ。
向けだ#むけだ、向けに、向けの#Empt./Empt./名/Empt./Empt.#X向けだY, with X as a specific target, object, subject in mind, do Y/X is often a noun for a specified type of person (e.g. elderly)/Y is often a verb like (作る・設計する・デザインする・など)/I.e. it expresses something like: this was planned or made with these people in mind#このマンションは一人暮らしの高齢者向けだ設計されています。
に連れて#につれて#動＋辞書形/名/Empt./Empt.#Xに連れてY, while some single minded (i.e. in a single direction) change X is happening, another single minded change Y happens/as X, then Y/Y has to be a natural consequence/-> Y cannot be a volitional#台風の接近に連れて、雨や風が強くなってきた。
に従って#にしたがって#動＋辞書形/名/Empt./Empt.#Xに従ってY, while some change X is happening, another change Y happens/unlike with に連れて X doesn't have to have to be a change in a single direction/Y is often a natural consequence#車のスピードが上がるに従って、事故の危険性も高くなる。
に伴って#にともなって#動＋辞書形/名＋に伴う＋名、名/Empt./Empt.#Xに伴ってY, alongside X, Y/Both X and Y describe changes/unlike with と共に X doesn't have to have to be a change in a single direction/not used with unnocitably incremental change, but rather change that can be noticed in its entirety/硬い言い方#メールが普及するに伴い、コミュニケーションの方法も変わってきた。
と共に#にともに#動＋辞書形/名/Empt./Empt.#Xと共にY, alongside X, Y/Both X and Y describe changes/と共に specifically is used with single direction changes/not used with unnocitably incremental change, but rather change that can be noticed in its entirety/硬い言い方#経済の回復と共に、人々の表情も明るくなってきた。
次第だ#しだいだ#Empt./名/Empt./Empt.#YはX次第だ,X次第でY, Y is decided based on X/if X changes the results or outcome of Y changes/used with things that have various differences or "wide" things/with 次第ではY Y describes the possiblity of one of the many possible outcomes#人生が楽しいかどうかは考え方次第だ(Whether life is joyous or not depends on the way one thinks)/この夏のトレーニング次第で秋の試合に勝てるかどうかが決まる。
に応じて#におうじて#Empt./名＋に応じた＋名、名/Empt./Empt.#Xに応じてY, Y changes (is changed) according to X/do Y, based on X/ do Y, keeping X in mind (but NOT with X in mind as in do Y FOR X)/X is something of that isn't the same (for everyone) (i.e. the age or stamina of different people within a group) of which one can expect certain fluctuations or changes/Y is some phrase of a thing that will be done in accordance with X#ご予算に応じてパーティーのメニューを決めます。/お子さんの年齢に応じて本を選んでください。
につけて#Empt.#動＋辞書形/Empt./Empt./Empt.#XにつけてY, whenever one does X or X is done, one gets (into) a certain mood or feeling Y/Y describes a "motion of the heart"/Special case: 何かにつけて is a customary usage to mean 何かがあるたびに, in this case Y doesn't have quite be a "movement of the heart"#この歌を聞くにつけて、心に希望が湧いてくる。/父は何かにつけて、若い頃外国で過ごした思い出を語る。
やら#Empt.#動＋辞書形/名/い形＋い/Empt.#XやらYやらZ, X,Y,Z are examples of a long list of things/All things belong to the same "group"/Emphasises that there is, was all sorts of stuff and thus can't be sorted or arranged/is used when the speaker cannot list all the things or believes to do so would be too much of a pain/-> see this entire things as an over counterexample to this, with mixed in little examples of exactly this phenomenon#勝ったチームの選手たちは、泣き出すやら飛び上がるやらさまざまに喜びを表した。
というか#Empt.#動＋普通形/名/い形＋い/な形#XというかYというか, it can be said (described) as both X and Y/Both X and Y describe, explain the situation but it's not clear which is more fitting and so two are highlighted#あの子は元気がいいというか落ち着きないというか、静かにじっとしてない子です。
にしても・にしろ・にせよ#Empt.#動＋普通形、ない形/名/Empt./Empt.#All of the things listed can be used as examples to ultimately say the same thing/The things listed belong to the same group that highlights the example/Can also be used with opposing things in the list (e.g. the same verb once positive, once negated) see ex./What comes after the list is often a decision or urging by the speaker/「にせよ」は少し硬い言い方#野菜にしても魚にしても、料理の材料は新鮮さが第一です。/将来家を買うにしろ買わないにしろ、彫金をしておこう。
といった#Empt.#Empt./名＋といった＋名/Empt./Empt.#Ignore the ＋といった from the formatting (only look at the thing under 名)!/Used at the end of a list of examples to summarise all the examples.#私はケーキ、ポテトチップ、ハンバーガーといったカロリーの高いものが大好きです。/「エコ」という言葉は、「環境にいい」といった意味で使われるようになった。
